  "text": "In Kubernetes v1.32.0, the in-tree CNI plugin code (formerly in pkg/kubelet/dockershim/network/cni/) was removed along with dockershim in v1.24. CNI integration is now fully delegated to the container runtime via CRI (Container Runtime Interface). The key files are: (1) kuberuntime_sandbox.go \u2014 creates pod sandboxes triggering CNI via CRI's RunPodSandbox, generates sandbox config with network namespace/port mappings, and determines pod IPs from sandbox status (IPAM results); (2) kuberuntime_manager.go \u2014 SyncPod orchestrates pod creation including sandbox creation, and UpdatePodCIDR passes the pod CIDR to the runtime for CNI/IPAM configuration; (3) util/util.go \u2014 configures network namespace mode (POD vs NODE) and detects sandbox changes requiring network re-setup; (4) instrumented_services.go \u2014 metrics-instrumented wrappers for RunPodSandbox and UpdateRuntimeConfig; (5) runtime.go \u2014 tracks network readiness state and pod CIDR; (6) cri-api services.go \u2014 defines PodSandboxManager and RuntimeService interfaces; (7) cri-client remote_runtime.go \u2014 the gRPC client making actual RunPodSandbox and UpdateRuntimeConfig calls to the container runtime.",
